ck Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of uncertain origin; it was not in general use before the late 18th century. It may be a Latinate variant of the biblical name   Adah .  However, it has also been explained as a pet form of   Adele   and   Adelaide  , Germanic female names of which the first element is <i>adal</i> ‘noble’. It was borne by a 7th-century abbess of Saint-Julien-des-Prés at Le Mans."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ada d’Engaine was born in 1122, in Cumberland, England, her father, William d'Engaine, was 22 and her mother, Eustachie, was 20. She married Simon de Morville about 1136, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died after 1169, in Burgh by Sands, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1122–after 1169":"1122–pärast 1169","1122–1169":"1122–1169","1118–1167":"1118–1167","1121–1195":"1121–1195","1138–1202":"1138–1202","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1101–1158":"1101–1158","1103–1158":"1103–1158","about 1140":"umbes 1140","1121":"1121","Bef 1158":"enne 1158","1140":"1140","1195":"1195","1118":"1118","1138":"1138","1158":"1158","1103":"1103","1202":"1202","1169":"1169","1168":"1168","1167":"1167","1101":"1101","1122":"1122","about 1136":"umbes 1136","about 1145":"umbes 1145","after 1169":"pärast 1169","Burgh-by-Sands, Cumberland, England":"Burgh by Sands, Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kirkowald, Cumbria, England":"Cumberland, England","Burgh by Sands, Cumberland, England":"Burgh by Sands, Cumberland, England","England":"England","Irthington, Cumberland, England":"Irthington, Cumberland, England","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1122–after 1169":"1122–1169 jälkeen","1122–1169":"1122–1169","1118–1167":"1118–1167","1121–1195":"1121–1195","1138–1202":"1138–1202","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1101–1158":"1101–1158","1103–1158":"1103–1158","about 1140":"noin 1140","1121":"1121","Bef 1158":"ennen vuotta 1158","1140":"1140","1195":"1195","1118":"1118","1138":"113